OpenGrammar
Copyright Swadhin Biswas and the OpenGrammar contributors
Source:  https://github.com/swadhinbiswas/opengrammar
License: Apache License, Version 2.0

This fork (https://github.com/zazzn/opengrammar) makes significant changes to
the upstream work, including but not limited to:

  - Inline mechanical-only correction tier rebuilt on the Automattic Harper
    local engine (offline, on-device), replacing the prior inline path.
  - A local n-gram context re-ranker for spelling candidate selection.
  - Grammar/tone moved to an explicit, non-inline button (whole-text LLM
    review via the backend /correct and /rewrite routes).
  - Additional LLM providers (e.g. Abacus RouteLLM), encrypted API-key
    storage, Ollama idle-unload controls, and assorted UX fixes.

A summary of changes is maintained in the project's operational notes.

